<subSubSection id="C32E65595C24FF8048A6FF48FE8AFEE0" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8B36D25C24FF8048A6FF48FE8AFEE0" blockId="59.[151,1436,151,285]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis id="B940EAC05C24FF8048A6FF48FEF5FF4D" bold="true" box="[199,315,151,176]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C344D515C24FF804AFBFF47FB95FF4D" authority="Santos &amp; Azevedo, 2000" authorityName="Santos &amp; Azevedo" authorityYear="2000" box="[666,1115,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breviramus">
<emphasis id="B940EAC05C24FF804AFBFF47FCF6FF4D" box="[666,824,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">A. breviramus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFA54B235C24FF804B21FF47FB95FF4D" box="[832,1115,151,176]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" refId="ref281771" refString="Santos, H. S. &amp; Azevedo, C. O. (2000) Sistematica das especies de Anisepyris Kieffer (Hymenoptera, Bethylidae) do Brasil. Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 44, 129 - 165." type="journal article">Santos &amp; Azevedo, 2000</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
only by having the pronotal disc with its transverse pronotal carina incomplete and the basal portion of the paramere narrow, whereas 
<taxonomicName id="4C344D515C24FF804DE5FF63FEDBFF05" authorityName="Santos &amp; Azevedo" authorityYear="2000" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breviramus">
<emphasis id="B940EAC05C24FF804DE5FF63FEDBFF05" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">A. breviramus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the pronotal disc with its transverse pronotal carina complete; and with the basal portion of the paramere wide.
</paragraph>
